Miles O'Brien joining us from
Boston tonight,

20:54.553 --> 20:55.221 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
thanks so much.

20:55.321 --> 20:57.123 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: You're welcome.

20:57.223 --> 21:01.327 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Now an
on-the-ground look.
We get that from Michal
Huniewicz, a Polish

21:01.427 --> 21:06.065 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
photographer living in England.
He visited
Chernobyl last year and
documented the effects

21:06.165 --> 21:10.236 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of the radiation on surrounding
villages,
plants, and animals.

21:10.336 --> 21:14.507 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This was personal for and you
your family.
Tell me a little bit about how
they were affected

21:14.607 --> 21:16.342 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
after the blast.

21:16.442 --> 21:18.477 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MICHAL HUNIEWICZ, Photographer:
I was 2 years
old when it happened, so I don't
remember

21:18.577 --> 21:20.346 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
a great deal.

21:20.446 --> 21:23.949 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But what I do know from my
parents was that,
when I was 2 years old, someone
knocked on

21:24.049 --> 21:30.022 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
our door in the middle of the
night and woke
up my parents. And they had to
wake me up

21:30.122 --> 21:34.593 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and give me something to drink,
which was
called the Lugol's solution, but
we didn't

21:34.693 --> 21:36.562 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
know at the time exactly what it
was.

21:36.662 --> 21:39.932 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And they didn't offer any
explanation to my
parents, other than, there was
some sort of

21:40.032 --> 21:44.303 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
environmental problem, and your
son, due to
his very young age, has to drink
it.

21:44.403 --> 21:48.040 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
After that, they disappeared,
because they
had to distribute it to other
children. It

21:48.140 --> 21:52.178 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
was only for people who were
very young, because,
when you're done, your thyroid
is unable to

21:52.278 --> 21:57.416 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
handle large doses of radiation.
If you're
a grownup, it is -- so it was
distributed

21:57.516 --> 21:59.285 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to children like myself.

21:59.385 --> 22:02.087 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Tell me a bit
about some
of the pictures that stand out
for you. I'm

22:02.188 --> 22:08.060 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
looking at a photo of a piano
that was left
in the same place. It looks like
a hospital

22:08.160 --> 22:11.163 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
infirmary and then what would be
baby bassinets.

22:11.263 --> 22:14.833 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MICHAL HUNIEWICZ: That was in a
place called
the Piano Shop. It wasn't
actually a piano

22:14.934 --> 22:19.004 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
shop in reality. That is just
the nickname
that the place was given.

22:19.104 --> 22:23.042 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's one of those places which
contains objects
which were never taken away.
There was quite

22:23.142 --> 22:27.213 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a large number of pianos. And
maybe you can
still play them, although I
suspect they are

22:27.313 --> 22:29.114 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
out of tune by now.

22:29.215 --> 22:34.186 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The hospital that you mentioned
was probably
the most eerie place, because we
do know for

22:34.286 --> 22:39.658 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a fact that there was where the
firefighters
were taken right after the
accident when they

22:39.758 --> 22:45.297 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
felt sick. They were brought to
the Moscow
hospital. They were shaved,
stripped. And

22:45.397 --> 22:50.836 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
later, they would be taken to
the Moscow Hospital
Number Six, which specializes in
radiation

22:50.936 --> 22:54.573 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
poisoning, acute radiation
poisoning.

22:54.673 --> 23:00.079 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
But the gear that those
firefighters were
wearing was dumped into basement
of the hospital.

23:00.179 --> 23:04.583 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That basement is pretty much
freely available.
It's probably one of the most
contaminated

23:04.683 --> 23:08.153 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
places on the planet, and you
can just walk
in there.

23:08.254 --> 23:16.695 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And a piece of headgear was
dragged up from
the basement to the lobby of
that building

23:16.795 --> 23:21.967 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
by someone. And it's lying on a
ledge, and
it's very highly radioactive.
So, there is

23:22.067 --> 23:28.574 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a picture of my hand with a
dosing meter getting
close to that piece of headgear.
I was really

23:28.674 --> 23:32.678 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
stressed, because the dosing
meter was very
loud. It was telling us, don't
go any nearer.

23:32.778 --> 23:37.616 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It was very highly radioactive.
So, that's
one of the most memorable
moments for me,

23:37.716 --> 23:39.551 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
because it was my hand close to
that object.

23:39.652 --> 23:44.990 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Finally, it
looks like Mother
Nature is winning. I mean,
everything that's

23:45.090 --> 23:47.660 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
unclaimed is being taken over by
plants.

23:47.760 --> 23:49.728 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MICHAL HUNIEWICZ: That's right.

23:49.828 --> 23:54.199 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You would imagine that the zone
would be destroyed
with nuclear fallout, but,
actually, it's

23:54.300 --> 24:00.673 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
become more of a sanctuary for
wildlife. There
is the Przewalski horses which
were brought

24:00.773 --> 24:05.377 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
after the accident, and half of
them died.
They didn't adjust. But the
other half has

24:05.477 --> 24:07.746 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
lived and they remain in the
zone.

24:07.846 --> 24:13.986 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They live wild. People do hunt
them, but they're
more or less allowed to live
undisturbed.

24:14.086 --> 24:19.792 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, indeed, the number of those
animals has
been growing, and they are doing
perfectly

24:19.892 --> 24:21.694 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
well.

24:21.794 --> 24:27.599 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I spoke to a scientist who
worked in the zone
trying to establish what the
impact was of

24:27.700 --> 24:32.071 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
radiation on those animal
species. And he
told me it was minuscule. There
was nothing

24:32.171 --> 24:37.676 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that he could detect. So, the
animals and
the plants live there without
any problems.

24:37.776 --> 24:39.745 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They are much better off without
humans.

24:39.845 --> 24:45.217 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, as you said, they are
taking over the
zone. There are trees growing
inside of buildings.

24:45.317 --> 24:49.722 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, I suspect, within a few
decades, there
will be not much left of the
zone, other than

24:49.822 --> 24:50.723 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the nuclear plant itself.

24:50.823 --> 24:52.458 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: All right.

24:52.558 --> 24:56.295 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Photographer Michal Huniewicz,
joining us
from London tonight, thanks so
much.

24:56.395 --> 25:06.805 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MICHAL HUNIEWICZ: Thank you for
having me.

25:06.905 --> 25:10.642 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Stay with us.

25:10.743 --> 25:16.415 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Coming up on the "NewsHour":
technology that
helps farmers reduce their
carbon footprint;

25:16.515 --> 25:23.088 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Burundian refugees hunted down
